falk@peregrine.Sun.COM (Ed Falk) writes:


>Among these regulations are various regulations against private
>point-to-point communications.  What you broadcast is for everybody to
>hear.  Ham and CB operators are allowed to address communications to
>specific individuals, but they still have to transmit in the clear.

Though this seems considerably watered down in recent years.  It used
to be pretty much absolute - if it went over the air you can listen to
it.  Within the last decade they seem to have decided this doesn't
apply to cellular phone communications however.

